Meghalaya Khasi Women dress:

In Shillong, the capital of Meghalaya, it is common to see women wearing the traditional Khasi dress called the "Jainsem" or "Dhara". 
On ceremonial occasions, they may wear a crown of silver or gold. A spike or peak consists decorative flowers and fixed to the back of the crown. 
The Jainsem consists of two pieces of material fastened at each shoulder and giving the body a cylindrical shape. 
The "Dhara" consists of a single piece of material also fastened at each shoulder.

The costume worn at traditional Khasi dances comprises ka jingpim shad, a single piece lungi like cloth draped from waist to ankle; 
ka sopti-kit, a full-sleeve blouse with lacework at the neck; 
and ka dhara rong ksiar, two rectangular pieces of cloth embroidered with gold thread, pinned crosswise at the shoulders, overlapping each other.



